FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1772892686
OL,3,CCouple in tears as 'shed' removed from
OL,4,Cfront garden following council battle
OL,6,FMr Holden said: "I just wanted to find
OL,7,Fsomewhere where I could develop my
OL,8,Felectronics and do household repairs
OL,9,Fand so on in peace and quiet and lend
OL,10,Ftools out to the neighbours but
OL,11,Fapparently I've got to find some other
OL,12,Fway to do that now."
OL,14,FMrs Holden said it has been "very
OL,15,Fstressful" and a "long process".
OL,17,FThe outdoor unit had been installed in
OL,18,F2020, built under the premise it's not
OL,19,Ftechnically a shed but a caravan
OL,20,Fbecause it can move, as it doesn't
OL,21,Fhave a fixed bottom.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1772892686
OL,3,CCouple in tears as 'shed' removed from
OL,4,Cfront garden following council battle
OL,6,FMr Holden previously hired a crane to
OL,7,Fdemonstrate that the structure could
OL,8,Fmove but the council rejected the
OL,9,Fargument and said it wasn't in keeping
OL,10,Fwith the local area.
OL,12,FToday, a crane arrived to take it away
OL,13,F(Friday 6 March).
OL,15,FNeighbour, Linda Revill, said: "Let's
OL,16,Fstrip it down to what it is.
OL,18,F"It's a shed in a private, well kept
OL,19,Fgarden, on a nice street, owned by a
OL,20,Fresponsible neighbour.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1772892686
OL,3,CCouple in tears as 'shed' removed from
OL,4,Cfront garden following council battle
OL,6,F"I cannot get my head around the fact
OL,7,Fthat the council and the planning
OL,8,Fofficer nor the powers that be have
OL,9,Ftaken so much time and resource to
OL,10,Fargue against this."
OL,12,FMr Holden added: "It was just a
OL,13,Fbuilding very much in keeping with the
OL,14,Fneighbourhood...but apparently the
OL,15,Fcouncil feel because it technically
OL,16,Fcontravenes planning permissions it
OL,17,Fhas to go."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
